      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 10:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and that with words of Scripture from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joel 3:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This passage (LXX. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 2:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", closely following the LXX.) treats of the coming in of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Messianic",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " era; hence Paul might refer ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κυρίου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which in the original points to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", justly ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to Christ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", who has appeared in the name of God, and continually rules as His Representative and Revealer, and Mediator, whose name was now the very specific object of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Christian",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " calling on the Lord. That Paul writes not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κυρίου",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is from no particular motive (against Hofmann); he simply reproduces the words of Scripture, which he presumes to be well known and makes his own.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
